jnxSpMIB.name: jnxSpMIB
jnxSpMIB.contactinfo: Juniper Technical Assistance Center Juniper Networks, Inc. 1194 N. Mathilda Avenue Sunnyvale, CA 94089 E-mail: support@juniper.net
jnxSpMIB.description: Provides data about each of the AS Pics on a router.

jnxSpSvcSet.name: jnxSpSvcSet
jnxSpSvcSet.description: Information about Service PIC Service Sets.

jnxSpSvcSetTable.name: jnxSpSvcSetTable
jnxSpSvcSetTable.description: Data about each service set on each Service PIC on the router.

jnxSpSvcSetEntry.name: jnxSpSvcSetEntry
jnxSpSvcSetEntry.description: Each entry provides information about a single Service Set. The Service Set is identified by its name and the Service PIC the Service Set is configured on is identified by jnxSpSvcSetIfName.

jnxSpSvcSetSvcType.name: jnxSpSvcSetSvcType
jnxSpSvcSetSvcType.description: The name of the Service Type associated with this table entry.

jnxSpSvcSetTypeIndex.name: jnxSpSvcSetTypeIndex
jnxSpSvcSetTypeIndex.description: A generic integer used to identify the Service Type for this entry.

jnxSpSvcSetIfName.name: jnxSpSvcSetIfName
jnxSpSvcSetIfName.description: The ifName of the interface identifying the Service PIC. If more than one interface is associated with the Service PIC, the name associated with the lowest layer interface is used for this object.

jnxSpSvcSetMemoryUsage.name: jnxSpSvcSetMemoryUsage
jnxSpSvcSetMemoryUsage.description: The amount of memory used by this Service Set, expressed in bytes.

jnxSpSvcSetCpuUtil.name: jnxSpSvcSetCpuUtil
jnxSpSvcSetCpuUtil.description: The amount of CPU used by this Service Set, expressed as a percentage of the total.

jnxSpSvcSetSvcStyle.name: jnxSpSvcSetSvcStyle
jnxSpSvcSetSvcStyle.description: The type of this Service Set. The definitions of each style being: Unknown - Service style is not known. Interface-service - Service style is interface based. Next-hop-service - Service style is next-hop based.

jnxSpSvcSetMemLimitPktDrops.name: jnxSpSvcSetMemLimitPktDrops
jnxSpSvcSetMemLimitPktDrops.description: The number of packets dropped due to the Service Set exceeding its memory limits (when in Red Zone).

jnxSpSvcSetCpuLimitPktDrops.name: jnxSpSvcSetCpuLimitPktDrops
jnxSpSvcSetCpuLimitPktDrops.description: The number of packets dropped due to the Service Set exceeding the average cpu limits (when total exceeds 85%).

jnxSpSvcSetFlowLimitPktDrops.name: jnxSpSvcSetFlowLimitPktDrops
jnxSpSvcSetFlowLimitPktDrops.description: The number of packets dropped due to the Service Set exceeding the flow limit.

jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeTable.name: jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeTable
jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeTable.description: Data about each service on each Service PIC on the router.

jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeEntry.name: jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeEntry
jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeEntry.description: Each entry provides information about a single Service on each Service PIC. Each Service PIC is identified by its corresponding ifIndex, while each Service is identified by jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeIndex. The Service Type associated with this index is provided by jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeName.

jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeIndex.name: jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeIndex
jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeIndex.description: A generic integer used to identify the Service Type for this entry.

jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeIfName.name: jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeIfName
jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeIfName.description: The ifName of the interface identifying the Service PIC. If more than one interface is associated with the Service PIC, the name associated with the lowest layer interface is used for this object.

jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeName.name: jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeName
jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeName.description: The name of the Service Type associated with this table entry.

jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeSvcSets.name: jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeSvcSets
jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeSvcSets.description: The number of Service Sets configured on this Service PIC that use this service type.

jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeMemoryUsage.name: jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeMemoryUsage
jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeMemoryUsage.description: The amount of memory used by this Service Type, expressed in bytes.

jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypePctMemoryUsage.name: jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypePctMemoryUsage
jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypePctMemoryUsage.description: The amount of memory used by this Service Type, expressed as a percentage of the total.

jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeCpuUtil.name: jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeCpuUtil
jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeCpuUtil.description: The amount of CPU used by this Service Type, expressed as a percentage of the total.

jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeMemoryUsage64.name: jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeMemoryUsage64
jnxSpSvcSetSvcTypeMemoryUsage64.description: The amount of memory used by this Service Type, expressed in bytes, represented by 64 bit integer.

jnxSpSvcSetIfTable.name: jnxSpSvcSetIfTable
jnxSpSvcSetIfTable.description: Service Set data about each Service PIC on the router.

jnxSpSvcSetIfEntry.name: jnxSpSvcSetIfEntry
jnxSpSvcSetIfEntry.description: Each entry provides Service Set information about a single Service PIC. Each Service PIC is identified by its corresponding ifIndex.

jnxSpSvcSetIfTableName.name: jnxSpSvcSetIfTableName
jnxSpSvcSetIfTableName.description: The ifName of the interface identifying the Service PIC. If more than one interface is associated with the Service PIC, the name associated with the lowest layer interface is used for this object.

jnxSpSvcSetIfSvcSets.name: jnxSpSvcSetIfSvcSets
jnxSpSvcSetIfSvcSets.description: The number of Service Sets configured on this Service PIC.

jnxSpSvcSetIfMemoryUsage.name: jnxSpSvcSetIfMemoryUsage
jnxSpSvcSetIfMemoryUsage.description: The amount of memory used by this Service PIC, expressed in bytes.

jnxSpSvcSetIfPctMemoryUsage.name: jnxSpSvcSetIfPctMemoryUsage
jnxSpSvcSetIfPctMemoryUsage.description: The amount of memory used by this Service PIC, expressed as a percentage of the total.

jnxSpSvcSetIfPolMemoryUsage.name: jnxSpSvcSetIfPolMemoryUsage
jnxSpSvcSetIfPolMemoryUsage.description: The amount of policy memory used by this Service PIC, expressed in bytes.

jnxSpSvcSetIfPctPolMemoryUsage.name: jnxSpSvcSetIfPctPolMemoryUsage
jnxSpSvcSetIfPctPolMemoryUsage.description: The amount of policy memory used by this Service PIC, expressed as a percentage of the total.

jnxSpSvcSetIfMemoryZone.name: jnxSpSvcSetIfMemoryZone
jnxSpSvcSetIfMemoryZone.description: The memory-usage zone currently occupied by this Service PIC. The definitions of each zone are: Green - All new flows are allowed. Yellow - Unused memory is reclaimed. All new flows are allowed. Orange - New flows are only allowed for service sets that are using less than their equal share of memory. Red - No new flows are allowed.

jnxSpSvcSetIfCpuUtil.name: jnxSpSvcSetIfCpuUtil
jnxSpSvcSetIfCpuUtil.description: The amount of CPU used by this Service PIC, expressed as a percentage of the total.

jnxSpSvcSetIfMemoryUsage64.name: jnxSpSvcSetIfMemoryUsage64
jnxSpSvcSetIfMemoryUsage64.description: The amount of memory used by this Service PIC, expressed in bytes, represented by 64 bit integer.

jnxSpSvcSetIfPolMemoryUsage64.name: jnxSpSvcSetIfPolMemoryUsage64
jnxSpSvcSetIfPolMemoryUsage64.description: The amount of policy memory used by this Service PIC, expressed in bytes, represented by 64 bit integer.

jnxSpNotificationPrefix.name: jnxSpNotificationPrefix
jnxSpNotificationPrefix.description: All collector notifications are registered under this branch.

jnxSpSvcSetZoneEntered.name: jnxSpSvcSetZoneEntered
jnxSpSvcSetZoneEntered.description: This indicates a Service PIC has entered a more severe memory-usage zone from a less severe memory usage zone. The zone entered is identified by jnxSpSvcSetIfMemoryZone.

jnxSpSvcSetZoneExited.name: jnxSpSvcSetZoneExited
jnxSpSvcSetZoneExited.description: This indicates a Service Pic has exited a more severe memory-usage zone to a less severe memory usage zone. The zone exited is identified by jnxSpSvcSetIfMemoryZone.

jnxSpSvcSetCpuExceeded.name: jnxSpSvcSetCpuExceeded
jnxSpSvcSetCpuExceeded.description: This indicates a Service Pic has exceeded its internal threshold for CPU utilization (85%).

jnxSpSvcSetCpuOk.name: jnxSpSvcSetCpuOk
jnxSpSvcSetCpuOk.description: This indicates a Service Pic has crossed below its internal threshold for CPU utilization (85%).

jnxSpSvcSetFlowLimitUtil.name: jnxSpSvcSetFlowLimitUtil
jnxSpSvcSetFlowLimitUtil.description: The Total no of flows present in this Service Set, expressed as a percentage of the total maximum flows.

jnxSpSvcSetFlowLimitUtilized.name: jnxSpSvcSetFlowLimitUtilized
jnxSpSvcSetFlowLimitUtilized.description: This indicates a Service Set has reached its upper limit of flows threshold of a maximun flows allowed for a service set.
